The Telegraph - Calcutta
 ICC plans ODI blitz in US
London: As part of its efforts to popularise cricket around the world, the International Cricket Council (ICC) is planning to organise a one-day championship involving the games biggest stars in the US. The ICC will work in tandem with the United States Cricket Association (USCA) and appoint a national chief executive officer, who will garner the support of top cricket playing nations to play in the US, according to an press release issued here on Friday. The plan is to focus on developing cricket as a successful niche sport in a substantial market, Malcolm Speed, chief executive of the ICC was quoted as saying in the release. The proceeds of the planned one-day tournament will go in for the development of the game in a country dominated by baseball, football, basketball and ice hockey, said Speed. (PTI)  Copyright 
